NUMBER 390
NAME Common Room
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large room is richly furnished with comfortable leather chairs,
brocaded lounges and several tables. The floor is marble, covered with fine
rugs and carpets. The walls have paintings of the Royal family, going back
many generations. Book cases are seen on several walls. A huge fireplace is
centered on the southern wall. A broad door provides exit back to the rest
of the Palace and two doors, on the south wall, one teak that has a crest
scrubbed away from it, and the other of polished oak inlaid with a Golden
Oak tree. The teak door has also been heavily barred and seems to be
impervious to any entry.
*DESCRIPTION_END
