NUMBER 1022
NAME Hadan's Study
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
A palable veil of darkness hangs over this entire room. It is undoubtedly
due to the furnishings, all of which are of dark material. The full-length
rug is a deep crimson color, embroidered with an image of a large black
dragon, spewing gouts of flame. A polished mirmach desk, painted jet black,
sits in front of a long bookcase containing various tomes dealing with
demons and necromancy. A high-backed chair, with a blood red leather cushion
sits pushed up against the desk. A door leads back out to the Common Room
and a black arch, engraved with detailed images of the various gods, leads
to the Royal Bedchamber.
*DESCRIPTION_END
