NUMBER 375
NAME Palace, grounds
MONSTER_GROUP 15
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A sand covered path leads from the gate to the front entrance of the
Royal Palace. Lining the path are beautiful flowers and trees are tended
to by the Royal gardener. His work is exemplary. One could spend many
hours just staring in wonderment at the profusion of flora. The palace
itself is the work of another artisan at the top of his profession.
Broad, blue marbled steps lead up to a series of fluted marble pillars.
The pillars and their entablature are sculpted to look like young nymphs.
Large, potted plants sit between the pillars, except for the entryway,
and the vines of the plants have started to grow their way up the pillars,
adding even more beauty to the palace. Through the front entryway, one
can see various functionaries running about. A gate leads back to the city.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 376
