ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Elm trees encircle a man-made tide pool on three sides. The fourth side
is a beach. The pool is filled with crystal clear water, and all
varieties of marine life can be seen in it. A Royal Game Warden
continuously watches over the pool to ensure that its fragile ecosystem
is maintained. The pool is a wonderful place to swim a few laps, or to
enjoy a few carefree hours of fishing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
